codex
Quick audit result:
- Security: no new external input surface; the verifier only re-reads local artifacts and fails closed on missing or malformed data.
- Performance: the added cost is two JSON history reads, one metrics read, and two checkpoint loads after training. That’s negligible next to the training loop and adds zero per-batch overhead.
- Regression: the smoke path still uses the same trainer/export flow; the only behavior change is stricter post-save validation, and the full miso `pytest` gate plus smoke run already covered that path.
Plan update
Post-save verification is implemented and the exact miso quality gates passed. Remaining work is repo bookkeeping and clean commit sequencing.
  ✓ Add failing tests for final saved-artifact completion verification and CLI promise ordering
  ✓ Implement minimal persisted-artifact verifier and invoke it before success emission
  → Run targeted tests, then full quality gates in miso, then audit/log/progress/commit
